sequenceDiagram
    participant SH as Shell (env vars)
    participant PY as Python n_tuples.py
    participant BIND as PyO3 cycles.rs
    participant FILT as Rust VertexFilter
    participant ENUM as Rust per_vertex DFS
    participant OUT as Output cycles

    SH->>PY: HSIKAN_VERTEX_FILTER=triangle<br/>HSIKAN_VERTEX_FILTER_MIN_DEGREE=2
    PY->>PY: read env, build filter_params dict
    PY->>BIND: enumerate_top_k_per_vertex_cycles_signed_rs(<br/>...edges, k, m, scorer, pruner,<br/>filter_kind="triangle", filter_params={...})
    Note over BIND: Macro-dispatch over<br/>(scorer × pruner × filter)
    BIND->>FILT: TriangleFilter.keep_set(g)
    FILT->>FILT: build adjacency dict<br/>(O(|E|))
    FILT->>FILT: per-vertex triangle count<br/>(O(|E|·d̄))
    FILT-->>BIND: Vec<u32> keep_set<br/>(e.g. 80k of 131k vertices)
    BIND->>ENUM: enumerate_top_k_per_vertex_cycles_par(<br/>g, k, m, pruner, scorer, filter)
    Note over ENUM: rayon par_iter over<br/>filter.keep_set() instead of 0..n_nodes
    ENUM->>ENUM: per-vertex DFS only on kept vertices<br/>(40-60% of vertices skipped)
    ENUM-->>BIND: Vec<Cycle>
    BIND->>BIND: subsample to max_cycles<br/>(via _subsample_arr_to_tuples,<br/>landed 2026-05-10)
    BIND-->>PY: numpy array (cap, k) + scores
    PY-->>OUT: list[SignedNTuple]
